PERSONNEL - Ald. Huels, Chairman (Cruts, Wisbrock, Jokerst)
Discussion regarding Annual Performance Evaluations.
Existing categories were reviewed for consistency and conciseness - hopefully creating a more user-friendly form. One (1) item that still needs to be addressed is whether the Board wants to retain or remove the "Exceeds Expectations" category.

Mayor Maurath expressed he was not in favor of keeping "exceeds" in the evaluation. Alderman Clauss asked if removed, how would you measure those employees who do go above and beyond. Alderman Huels suggested considering removing "exceeds" from certain categories. Alderman Cruts agreed with Alderman Clauss that the City needs to acknowledge efforts but should not be abused or customary. Comments could be made noting accomplishments above and beyond. Alderman Clauss expressed she feels an atmosphere has been created that employees are expected to perform above and beyond, and if an employee is not rewarded for that what is the incentive for an employee to do so. Alderman Bereitschaft agreed "exceeds" does not apply to all categories.

City Administrator Nikki Finkbiner shared evaluations are used for merit raises. She feels if across the board raise is utilized, there is no need for "exceeds" on the evaluation as all employees received the same amount for a raise.

Alderman Maserang stated he feels some employees do exceed and merit raises should be utilized.

Alderman Clauss inquired if the Board feels the person completing the form is not competent and if so that concern needs to be addressed not the form. Alderman Wisbrock suggested moving forward with the proposed form with "exceeds" and provide further education to those who are completing the form.

Following discussion, Alderman Huels made a motion to continue the discussion of Annual Performance Evaluations to the October Board of Aldermen Committee Meeting. The motion was seconded by Alderman Wisbrock. Upon a voice vote being taken, it was announced that the motion was passed unanimously by the Committee.

