Consideration of a request for City shirts.
At the August 3, 2023, Board of Aldermen Committee meeting, it was requested that Staff explore local Fenton businesses, shirt styles, prices, and logos for City shirts for Boards, Committees, Commissions, and Department Heads as it would be nice to see the City identified at events, similar to other municipalities.

Staff met with local vendor S&S Graphics, Inc., which is located on Fenpark Drive. Examples of the types of embroidered shirts that S&S Graphics can provide were available for review, and they are open to the public so anyone wanting a shirt can go into the store to physically see the materials and sizes.

S&S Graphics can also offer a customized online store account, that allows any authorized person to order their preferred shirt, with an approved logo. The City will then be invoiced.

At this time, Staff is requesting that the Board approve using S&S Graphics to supply the City's shirts and suggests the Board authorize a maximum amount that each authorized individual can spend (example: $40 per person.)

There was a discussion about the logoto be Fenton City of Parks only or Fenton City of Parks with department under the logo and if shirts should be one color for consistency or offer a variety of colors.

City Administrator Nikki Finkbiner clarified if the Board wanted to include volunteer positions for City shirts and inquired if there should be a policy in place. She noted she was uncomfortable and concerned with a generic blanket City logo without position, as a statement may be misconstrued. Discussion ensued regarding adding titles to the shirts.

Planning and Zoning Commission member Deb Abbott shared she is in favor of shirts being all the same color to be easily identifiable with department under logo.

Following discussion, Alderman Bereitschaft made a motion to forward to the September Board of Aldermen meeting the consideration to use S&S Graphics to supply City shirts and authorize $40.00 per individual. The motion was seconded by Alderman Maserang.

Alderman Maserang rescinded his second. Alderman Bereitschaft rescinded his motion.

Alderman Wisbrock stated he was in favor of having the title on the shirt.

Alderman Bereitschaft made a motion to forward to the September Board of Aldermen meeting the consideration to use S&S Graphics to supply City shirts with Fenton City of Parks logo with department listed under logo, online store or in-store availability, with a variety of colors, and authorize $40.00 per individual. The motion was seconded by Alderman Maserang. Upon a voice vote being taken, it was announced that the motion was passed unanimously by the Committee.

Consideration of proposals for a new monument sign in front of City.
At the July 13 Committee Meeting, the Community Development and Affairs Committee approved Staff seeking proposals for a new, non-digital sign for City Hall via a Request for Proposals (RFP). The RFP was advertised in late July and the deadline for submittals was on August 17th.

Although ten (10) companies requested a copy of the RFP, only two (2) proposals were received. It is noted that the RFP allowed the sign company to design the sign and give a base bid price. It was noted in the RFP that while cost would be considered, the City plans to award the bid to the contractor that provides a proposal that best reflects the character of the City of Fenton.

The proposals received from Warren Sign Company and Piros Sign, Inc. were available for review.
- The base bid price provided by Warren Sign Company is $32,539.
- The base bid price provided by Piros Sign is $15,894 (for the A2 option), with alternate options at $22,126 (Al) and $35,046 (A3).

It is noted that Piros Signs was the company used by the City for the digital sign located in front of RiverChase and Piros was also recently used by the YMCA to produce all the exterior/interior signs for RiverChase YMCA.

Following discussion, Alderman Bereitschaft made a motion to continue to the October Board of Aldermen Committee meeting the proposal from Warren Sign Company for a new monument sign in front of City with standoff lettering, acrylic, interior backlighting and gather additional information including warranty. The motion was seconded by Alderman Harrell. Upon a voice vote being taken, it was announced that the motion was passed unanimously by the Committee.

